HEADWORD: Unhorse
<hw>Un*horse"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>horse</ets>.]</ety> <def>To throw from a horse; to
cause to dismount; also, to take a horse or horses from; <as>as, to
<ex>unhorse</ex> a rider; to <ex>unhorse</ex> a carriage</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

